{"hash":"f60f81fcd5a11bef756902ea798e1e190db10bbe","data":{"page":{"title":"Introduction","content":"<h2 id=\"introduction\"><a href=\"#introduction\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Introduction</h2>\n<p>Source plugin for fetching data from a GIT repository. This source is based on the @gridsome/source-filesystem and includes all functionality which is available in the @gridsome/source-filesystem.</p>\n<p>This is a port from Gatsby: <a href=\"https://github.com/stevetweeddale/gatsby-source-git\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">stevetweeddale/gatsby-source-git</a>, but extended to enable the clone of private git repositories.</p>\n<h2 id=\"installation\"><a href=\"#installation\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Installation</h2>\n<div class=\"gridsome-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\"><span class=\"token function\">npm</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span> -s @noxify/gridsome-source-git</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"usage\"><a href=\"#usage\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Usage</h2>\n\n          <div class=\"gridsome-code-title codeblock-title\">\n            <span>gridsome.config.js</span>\n          </div>\n         \n<div class=\"gridsome-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">module<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>exports <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  plugins<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      use<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'@noxify/gridsome-source-git'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n      options<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        remote<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'https://github.com/noxify/test.git'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        target<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'git-source/noxify-test/'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        typeName<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'GitPost'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        route<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'/gitpost/:id'</span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"supported-provider\"><a href=\"#supported-provider\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Supported provider</h2>\n<p>We have tested the plugin with:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Github</li>\n<li>GitLab</li>\n<li>Bitbucket</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"supported-repository-types\"><a href=\"#supported-repository-types\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Supported Repository types</h2>\n<p>The source plugin supports <code class=\"language-text\">public</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">private</code> repositories.</p>\n"},"repo":{"title":"GIT Source","content":"<p>Gridsome source to fetch data from a remote git repository</p>\n","repository":"noxify/gridsome-source-git"},"sidebar":{"edges":[{"node":{"category":[{"id":"4ee85a59","title":"Getting started","links":[{"id":"f261bcf0","title":"Introduction","url":""},{"id":"92c289c4","title":"Configuration","url":"/configuration"}]},{"id":"2b1e1f88","title":"Examples","links":[{"id":"5568a9b3","title":"Public Repository","url":"/example-public-repo"},{"id":"1d644080","title":"Private Repository","url":"/example-private-repo"}]}]}}]}},"context":{"id":"dbcadfbf7c13f63e039e91ed7cc8554c","plugin":"gridsome-source-git","pluginId":"gridsome-source-git"}}